# IT Support Troubleshooting Guide

This repository contains structured troubleshooting procedures for common corporate IT issues.  
It is designed to simulate an internal IT support knowledge base used by service desk teams.

## Purpose
To document repeatable troubleshooting processes that improve response time, consistency and service quality in corporate IT environments.

## Scope
This guide covers:

- Printer connectivity issues
- Slow computer performance
- Network detection failures
- Outlook email sending issues
- WiFi connectivity problems

Each article follows a structured format used in enterprise IT teams:
Problem → Diagnosis → Resolution → Prevention → Business Impact
